wiki.content: “CARNIVAL” (initially “H00LIGANS”) is the twelfth track from VULTURES 1 and features Rich The Kid & Playboi Carti. The track was originally previewed at the Las Vegas Vultures Rave on December 15th, 2023. A newer version was later previewed at the Vultures Listening Party held in Chicago’s United Center on February 8th, 2024. This song features a new choir background, a new instrumental, an altered Rich The Kid and Kanye verse, and an entirely new feature by Playboi Carti. This version of the track was played at the February 9th Vultures Listening Party at the UBS Center in New York, after Carti made a surprise appearance on the stage. Kanye West also samples his own song “Hell of a Life” in this song due to the original sample by Ozzy Osbourne not being cleared announced via a public ouburst. The Carnival Pack EP Cover which the song is featured on, has an album cover of a ‘Inter Milan Ultra fan chanting the chorus of the song. A group of 'Inter Milan fans sung the backing chorus of the song; An interpolation of Rich The Kid’s Chorus. Read more on Last.fm.
